{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This is primarily a module handoff/orchestration risk (collectors -> merger -> summary input), which unit tests on single functions can miss. It does not require real OS/network/subprocess behavior in the behavior text, and it does not require judging real LLM output quality. Rejected System because the behavior does not require external contract/round-trip verification; rejected Agentic because it checks input payload composition, not model decision quality.","test_description":"Run the real data-collection orchestration with three source adapters wired (using deterministic test doubles for source responses), then assert the exact payload passed into summary generation contains all three source sections and key fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure handling here is cross-module (source error propagation -> report assembler fallback), which is beyond single-function unit logic. The behavior text does not explicitly require real external error-contract validation, and correctness is about fallback behavior, not LLM output quality. Rejected System because no explicit external error-shape or external round-trip effect is required; rejected Agentic because the assertion is on fallback note presence and non-abort behavior, not model judgment.","test_description":"Wire the reporting pipeline with one source adapter forced to fail (e.g., timeout/connection error) and the other two returning valid data; assert run completes, report is emitted, and the missing section contains `data unavailable`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","required_reality_check_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is directly about summary factual quality, which depends on real model output behavior and can vary run-to-run. Stubs would hide exactly the risk being tested. Rejected Workflow because behavior asks for single-output summary accuracy, not multi-step model-dependent state consistency across steps.","test_description":"Use representative real input datasets with known key values and run the real summary model/API; score outputs against factual-accuracy checks (key numbers/entities preserved, no contradictions/hallucinated values) over multiple trials to account for nondeterminism.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","required_reality_check_level":"System","justification":"This explicitly requires an externally visible side effect (email delivered to inbox) and therefore needs real round-trip verification at the boundary. Unit/integration with mocked mail transport can give false confidence. Rejected Agentic because this behavior’s pass condition is delivery/readback correctness, not evaluating model output quality.","test_description":"Execute the full scheduled report run in a test environment with real delivery infrastructure to a test mailbox; verify via real inbox readback (IMAP/provider API) that the message arrives for configured recipients with expected subject/body/report attachment or content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"The core risk is orchestration/state handoff across components (delivery failure -> local persistence -> next-run retry), which is best validated by wiring modules together with filesystem persistence. The behavior text does not explicitly require validating real external error contracts or real inbox round-trip for this scenario. Rejected System because no explicit external contract/readback requirement is stated; rejected Agentic/Workflow because no model-output-quality or multi-agentic-step dependency is described.","test_description":"Run two sequential scheduler invocations in a test harness: first with mail client failing unreachable to assert report is persisted on local filesystem; second with mail client restored to assert persisted report is retried and marked sent/cleared.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.28,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
